\cf2 To maintain system hygiene and ensure that the end-user dashboard remained focused on relevant projects, a sophisticated filtering mechanism was engineered. A constant \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 SYSTEM_REPOS\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  array\'97comprising \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 appcentral\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 base\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 pipelines\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 , and \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 terraform\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \'97was integrated into the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 get-dashboard-projects.ts\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  logic. This programmatic exclusion ensures that critical infrastructure repositories are not inadvertently modified or cluttered by standard users, maintaining a clear separation between the platform's core and the projects it hosts.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 DraftCentral: Workflow Compression and the FastTrack Initiative\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 DraftCentral represents a shift toward the "intelligent automation" of administrative workflows. The cornerstone of this project during the 2026 tenure was the 
\f0\b FastTrack
\f1\b0  initiative, developed within the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 feat/fasttrack-resq-reimagined\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  branch. The objective was to reimagine the document drafting flow by compressing a traditional multi-step wizard into a single-input interface.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This required the development of complex frontend logic capable of parsing intent and data from a unified entry point, thereby reducing the number of user interactions required to generate a finalized draft. The engineering work involved:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Logic Re-engineering:
\f1\b0  Moving away from a sequential state-machine toward a more declarative input model that could infer the necessary selection screens from the initial input.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 State Persistence:
\f1\b0  Utilizing AWS RDS for PostgreSQL to maintain draft integrity across sessions, ensuring that even if a user disconnected during the "FastTrack" process, their progress was cached and recoverable.\
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Testing Rigor:
\f1\b0  Implementing unit tests using the Jest framework to validate the robustness of the single-input parser, ensuring that edge cases in user input did not lead to malformed document outputs.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The successful transition of DraftCentral from a development-focused POC to a test-ready product culminated in a department-wide handover on February 5, 2026. This involved synchronizing the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 dev\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  branch into the \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 testing\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  branch and providing extensive technical documentation on local setup using Docker Compose and AWS RDS connectivity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 AgentCentral: Orchestrating Agentic AI Workflows\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 AgentCentral serves as the BIA\'92s exploration into the "Frontier" of agentic AI. Unlike traditional LLM applications that rely on static prompts, AgentCentral utilizes 
\f0\b n8n
\f1\b0  to orchestrate autonomous agents capable of performing multi-step tasks. The core focus was to investigate how agentic workflows could be governed and scaled within a government context, moving past the limitations of single-turn reasoning.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The technical investigation focused on three primary agentic patterns within the n8n ecosystem:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Orchestrator Pattern:
\f1\b0  A central "supervisor" agent that interprets user goals and delegates sub-tasks to specialized agents (e.g., an Email Agent or a Policy Analyst Agent).\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Chained Request Logic:
\f1\b0  Sequential flows where the output of one AI node feeds directly into the reasoning module of the next, allowing for deeper multi-stage analysis of complex government documents.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Human-in-the-Loop Integration:
\f1\b0  The creation of nodes that pause the autonomous workflow to wait for a public officer\'92s approval before high-stakes actions, such as drafting a response to a member or committing code to a repository.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf2 By utilizing n8n\'92s hybrid low-code/pro-code environment, the team was able to build modular subflows that leveraged external libraries and custom JavaScript to extend the capabilities of standard AI nodes. This approach allows for the rapid prototyping of "intelligent" services that can interact with internal legacy systems via HTTP requests while maintaining the flexibility of a modern AI backbone.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Business & Public Service Impact: Mapping to Smart Nation 2.0 Pillars\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 Singapore\'92s Smart Nation 2.0 vision is built on three foundational goals: Trust, Growth, and Community. The work performed within the Frontier Products Team contributes directly to these objectives by hardening digital infrastructure, accelerating innovation, and fostering a more inclusive digital society.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Trust: Hardening Infrastructure and Securing Identity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 Trust in a Smart Nation is contingent upon the reliability and security of its digital systems. The engineering contributions to AppCentral were centered on building a secure ecosystem through:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Identity Assurance:
\f1\b0  The integration of 
\f0\b Microsoft Entra ID (OIDC/OAuth)
\f1\b0  via \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 next-auth v5\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  ensured that only authorized public officers could access internal tools. This aligns with the national emphasis on Singpass and other trusted digital identities to safeguard data and simplify transactions.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 System Resilience:
\f1\b0  By moving to an API-first project tracking system and implementing strict input validation (regex-based project and domain names), the platform was hardened against common attack vectors like SQL injection and malformed URL exploits.\
\ls3\ilvl0
