\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Deep-Dive Interview: Senior Technical Architect Review\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf2 This section simulates a technical review session with a Senior Architect, focusing on the engineering nuances and strategic reasoning behind the 2026 internship accomplishments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Question 1: Architectural Logic of AppCentral\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 Interviewer:
\f1\b0  "You made the architectural decision to bypass a traditional database for project metadata in AppCentral, opting instead to query the Azure DevOps API directly. Given that API calls introduce latency and dependency on external services, what was your rationale for this 'stateless' metadata approach?"\

\f0\b Candidate:
\f1\b0  The rationale was rooted in the need for a "single source of truth." In previous iterations, we observed "state drift" where a database entry for a repository would exist, but the repository itself had been deleted or modified in Azure DevOps by an administrator. By making the AzDO API the primary provider of metadata, we ensured that the dashboard was always 100% accurate. To mitigate latency, I implemented skeleton loaders for a better user experience and explored server-side caching strategies. The trade-off of a few hundred milliseconds of network latency was well worth the elimination of data integrity issues.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Question 2: Docker and Networking Complexity\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 Interviewer:
\f1\b0  "You encountered a build-time issue with Cloudflare and \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 npm install\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  within your Docker containers. Can you explain the technical root cause and how your resolution balanced security with development velocity?"\

\f0\b Candidate:
\f1\b0  The root cause was an SSL verification conflict where the Cloudflare proxy headers were interfering with the npm registry's handshake inside a restricted container network. This led to permission errors that blocked the build process. My resolution involved a documented toggle: disabling the proxy during the initial \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 npm install\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  phase and immediately re-enabling it once the dependencies were cached. This ensured that we didn't lower our security posture for the runtime environment while still allowing the build pipeline to proceed without interruption.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Question 3: Security and Identity Management\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 Interviewer:
\f1\b0  "You implemented Microsoft Entra ID with \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 next-auth v5\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 . How did you handle session persistence and security when users navigate between different BIA products, and how does this align with the Board's wider move toward Zero-Trust?"\

\f0\b Candidate:
\f1\b0  Using \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 next-auth v5\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2  allowed us to leverage OIDC for secure token exchange. We configured the session management to utilize server-side JWTs, which are checked against the Entra ID provider on every route transition. This aligns with Zero-Trust principles because the application never assumes a session is valid; it constantly verifies the user\'92s identity and permissions. Furthermore, by using TechPass for single sign-on across the SGTS, we ensured that a user\'92s session in AppCentral was tied to their overall government digital identity.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 Question 4: Agentic Workflow Design\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf2 Interviewer:
\f1\b0  "In your work with AgentCentral and n8n, you explored the 'Orchestrator Pattern.' Why is this pattern more suitable for government workflows than a single monolithic agent with a massive toolset?"\

\f0\b Candidate:
\f1\b0  A monolithic agent with too many tools suffers from "context saturation," which often leads to hallucinations or the incorrect selection of tools. In a government environment\'97where accuracy in policy interpretation is non-negotiable\'97the Orchestrator Pattern is superior because it modularizes responsibility. The Orchestrator agent acts as a router, identifying the user's intent and calling a specialized sub-agent (e.g., a "Legal Specialist" or an "Internal Audit Agent") that has a narrow, highly-tuned prompt and a limited toolset. This makes the system more predictable, easier to audit, and much more scalable.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

