The shift toward API-first architectures and autonomous agent systems reflects a proactive approach to solving structural inefficiencies within the public sector. By adhering to the pillars of Smart Nation 2.0\'97Trust, Growth, and Community\'97the technical contributions provided during this period do not merely represent code committed to a repository, but a meaningful impact on how the CPFB Board and the Government as a whole serve the citizens of Singapore. As these "Frontier" products move from the Business Incubator into wide-scale production, the foundations laid in security, scalability, and agentic orchestration will remain central to the Board\'92s ongoing digital transformation.\
